In a sauce pan over medium heat, melt the butter and add the minced scallions and the bulgur. Saute for 1-2 minutes. Stir frequently. Add the sherry and stir. Add the chicken stock and let it slowly come to a boil stirring frequently. Add the frozen spinach and lemon pepper. Cook until spinach has thawed and the liquids come back to the boil (6-10 minutes). Remove from heat. Add the Parmesan cheese and serve. Or cover and keep in a 200 degrees F oven until ready to serve (up to 15 minutes).